abstract.value: The Gathering of the Tribes Archive includes correspondence, manuscripts, ephemera, photographic material, business and administrative records, video, audio, legal and financial records related to the operations of A Gathering of the Tribes, a literary magazine, gallery and performance space in New York's East Village.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the
following form:<lb/><lb/>
Identification of item,  date (if known); Gathering of the Tribes Archive; MSS 198; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.
The Gathering of the Tribes Archive was purchased by NYU's Fales Library and Special Collections from Steve Cannon in 2007.
For more information, please visit http://www.tribes.org .

The Gathering of the Tribes Archive contains correspondence, manuscripts, ephemera, photographic material, business and administrative records, video, audio, legal and financial records. Materials in the archive document the operations of A Gathering of the Tribes, a literary magazine, gallery and performance space, and its publishing imprint, Fly By Night Press. The collection is arranged into seven series:<lb/><lb/><emph render="bold">Series I: Media</emph> contains the audiovisual portion of the collection, inclusing video and audio cassettes.<lb/><lb/><emph render="bold">Series II: Scrapbooks</emph> contains binders of material compiled by Tribes employees related to the gallery space, including ephemera, photographic material and event documentation.<lb/><lb/><emph render="bold">Series III: Project Files</emph> contains files related to events, publications, and exhibitions, including correspondence, ephemera, artists' portfolios, and manuscripts.<lb/><lb/><emph render="bold">Series IV: Grant Applications</emph> contains the records of all grant applications drafted by A Gathering of the Tribes.<lb/><lb/><emph render="bold">Series VI: Publications</emph> contains printed material either published by, or associated with, A Gathering of the Tribes and Fly By Night Press.<lb/><lb/><emph render="bold">Series VII: Data Storage</emph> contains electronic media, including compact discs and floppy discs.

Series I: MediaScope and Content

This series contains audiovisual materials related to A Gathering of the Tribes, many containing footage of poetry and jazz performances in the Tribes Gallery and elsewhere.

Arrangement

Items were given individual ID numbers and described at the item level. Titles are arranged chronologically.

Conditions Governing Access

Audiovisual materials have not been preserved and may not be available to researchers.
